# Server Environment Variables (Vercel Deployment)

## Required Variables

| Variable | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `NODE_ENV` | Environment mode | `production` |
| `DATABASE_URL` | Neon PostgreSQL connection string | `postgresql://user:pass@host/db?sslmode=require` |
| `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET` | 32+ character secret for Better Auth | Generate: `openssl rand -base64 32` |
| `BETTER_AUTH_URL` | Deployed server URL (no trailing slash) | `https://your-server.vercel.app` |
| `CORS_ORIGIN` | Web app URL for CORS | `https://your-web.vercel.app` |

## Optional Variables (Email OTP)

| Variable | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `BREVO_API_KEY` | Brevo/SendinBlue API key for email sending | From Brevo dashboard |
| `BREVO_SENDER_EMAIL` | Verified sender email in Brevo | `noreply@yourdomain.com` |

## Generate BETTER_AUTH_SECRET

```bash
openssl rand -base64 32
```

## Deployment Steps

1. Deploy server to Vercel first
2. Note the server URL (e.g., `https://your-server.vercel.app`)
3. Deploy web app with `NEXT_PUBLIC_SERVER_URL` pointing to the server
